00:26:38,240 --> 00:26:40,800
I know. Hello, captain.

463
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:42,833
How you doing?

464
00:26:43,040 --> 00:26:45,713
- I need to talk to you.
- Okay.

465
00:26:46,040 --> 00:26:48,235
JOCELYN: Oh, my God, Raymond,
it's been so many years.

466
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:49,998
RAYMOND: And?
JOCELYN: And I've been married,

467
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:51,269
- I've been divorced.
RAYMOND: Yeah.

468
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:53,391
Well, you may have noticed
I've changed a bit myself.

469
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:57,070
No. No, that's not...
No, yes, I have noticed.

470
00:26:57,280 --> 00:27:01,068
I see. It's great.
Congratulations.

471
00:27:01,280 --> 00:27:02,713
My feelings haven't, though.

472
00:27:05,160 --> 00:27:07,469
Changed, I mean.

473
00:27:09,120 --> 00:27:12,271
What feelings? What?

474
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:15,630
Jocelyn, I have never
stopped wondering

475
00:27:15,840 --> 00:27:18,957
how things might have turned out
between us

476
00:27:19,160 --> 00:27:21,674
- if my mother hadn't...
- Raymond.

477
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:24,269
Raymond, people can't just
rewrite their lives.

478
00:27:26,360 --> 00:27:28,999
I haven't had a relationship...

479
00:27:29,200 --> 00:27:31,475
...of any consequence
since we stopped seeing each other.

480
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:34,035
Doesn't that say something to you?

481
00:27:34,840 --> 00:27:37,559
Yeah, that...

482
00:27:37,760 --> 00:27:41,196
That you must be just about
the loneliest person on this earth.

483
00:27:42,080 --> 00:27:45,550
Raymond, we were kids then. It must
have been, what, 15 years ago?

484
00:27:45,760 --> 00:27:46,829
It was sweet, but...

485
00:27:47,680 --> 00:27:48,999
Joce.

486
00:27:49,800 --> 00:27:52,268
Yeah. I have to go.

487
00:27:52,840 --> 00:27:53,875
Yeah.

488
00:27:54,080 --> 00:27:55,479
Best of luck with the campaign.

489
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:57,149
Thank you.

490
00:28:01,320 --> 00:28:02,673
Joce...

491
00:28:02,880 --> 00:28:05,314
Sergeant Raymond Shaw.

492
00:28:09,280 --> 00:28:11,316
I wanna talk to you too.

493
00:28:13,560 --> 00:28:14,709
- Not now.
- Excuse me, sir.

494
00:28:14,920 --> 00:28:16,353
I mean, I know you're busy,
congressman...

495
00:28:16,560 --> 00:28:18,357
- Don't touch me.
- I'm sorry.

496
00:28:18,560 --> 00:28:21,393
I'm sorry, it's just that, well...

497
00:28:21,600 --> 00:28:23,477
Don't ever touch me.

498
00:28:27,280 --> 00:28:29,840
ANDERSON: Hello, major.
Have you tried the Pad Thai?

499
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:32,594
I'm told it rules.

500
00:28:40,320 --> 00:28:42,276
MAN: <i>What were you hoping</i>
<i>Congressman Shaw would say?</i>

501
00:28:42,680 --> 00:28:44,318
I don't know, sir.

502
00:28:45,400 --> 00:28:49,359
It's not so much what he said
or didn't say, it was more of his...

503
00:28:49,560 --> 00:28:51,118
...attitude, his demeanor.

504
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:52,794
Are you taking your meds?

505
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:55,116
MARCO: Lieutenant Colonel Howard,
with all due respect,

506
00:28:55,320 --> 00:28:57,197
I've had over a dozen years
of experts telling me

507
00:28:57,400 --> 00:29:00,039
that I have Gulf War Syndrome,
I have post-traumatic stress disorder

508
00:29:00,240 --> 00:29:03,312
and every other mood disorder
that you can name.

509
00:29:03,520 --> 00:29:06,796
In those 12 years,
I've been a good soldier.

510
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:09,912
And I've denied what
every nerve ending in my body

511
00:29:10,120 --> 00:29:11,792
is telling me is more real than not.

512
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:14,195
I've had one dream,
not variations on a dream,

513
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:15,913
the same dream.
Night after night...

514
00:29:16,120 --> 00:29:19,032
No. No. I'm sorry.

515
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:21,595
You're saying that an entire squad
of U.S. Army soldiers

516
00:29:21,800 --> 00:29:23,631
was hypnotized into believing
that Raymond Shaw

517
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:25,353
deserved the Medal of Honor.

518
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:28,154
And that somehow,
thanks to your dream,

519
00:29:28,360 --> 00:29:30,794
you're the only one
who knows the truth.

520
00:29:31,520 --> 00:29:34,432
Major Marco, you will stay clear
of Congressman Shaw.

521
00:29:39,760 --> 00:29:42,513
HOWARD:
And you are to resume your medication.

522
00:29:42,720 --> 00:29:44,517
That is an order.

523
00:29:44,720 --> 00:29:46,199
GARRET:
That will be all, major.

524
00:29:46,880 --> 00:29:49,758
RAYMOND: <i>Somewhere right now,</i>
<i>an American soldier in the war on terror</i>

525
00:29:49,960 --> 00:29:52,190
<i>is worried about his</i>
<i>family back home.</i>

526
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:55,832
<i>Somewhere right now,</i>
<i>in some small American town,</i>

527
00:29:56,040 --> 00:29:58,679
<i>his grandmother is standing</i>
<i>in her kitchen.</i>

528
00:29:58,880 --> 00:30:01,348
<i>She's got her medicine bottle</i>
<i>in one hand,</i>

529
00:30:01,560 --> 00:30:04,791
<i>she's opening the refrigerator</i>
<i>with the other and she's thinking:</i>

530
00:30:05,720 --> 00:30:07,915
<i>"I can pay for my medicine...</i>

531
00:30:08,920 --> 00:30:10,990
<i>... or I can pay for my dinner.</i>

532
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:13,871
<i>I can't do both. "</i>

533
00:30:14,280 --> 00:30:16,157
<i>I don't believe that our mothers</i>
<i>and grandmothers</i>

534
00:30:16,360 --> 00:30:19,272
<i>should have to face that kind of</i>
<i>decision, not in this country.</i>

535
00:30:21,280 --> 00:30:24,272
<i>I don't believe that the brave men</i>
<i>and women of our armed forces,</i>

536
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:26,948
<i>risking their lives overseas,</i>
<i>should have to worry</i>

537
00:30:27,720 --> 00:30:31,110
<i>about their families back here</i>
<i>in America.</i>

538
00:30:32,160 --> 00:30:34,276
<i>You see, there are some gaps</i>
<i>in this country...</i>

539
00:30:35,440 --> 00:30:38,193
<i>... deep chasms</i>
<i>that we need to bridge.</i>

540
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:41,678
<i>The gap between rich and poor,</i>

541
00:30:42,040 --> 00:30:45,237
<i>between government</i>
<i>and the people,</i>

542
00:30:45,440 --> 00:30:48,671
<i>between true security</i>
<i>and the notion of feeling safe.</i>

543
00:30:48,880 --> 00:30:50,996
Second floor, room three,
end of hall.

544
00:30:51,480 --> 00:30:53,869
RAYMOND [ON TV]:
<i>Between what is real...</i>

545
00:30:54,080 --> 00:30:55,479
Don't you just love this guy?

546
00:30:55,680 --> 00:30:57,272
<i>And what is not.</i>

547
00:30:58,360 --> 00:31:00,920
<i>Tough choices are an unavoidable</i>
<i>element of leadership,</i>

548
00:31:01,120 --> 00:31:03,588
<i>I would just urge the governor</i>
<i>to remember that</i>

549
00:31:03,800 --> 00:31:07,190
<i>the primary responsibility</i>
<i>of government...</i>

550
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:09,356
[WOMAN MOANING NEARBY]

551
00:31:25,400 --> 00:31:27,356
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

552
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:30,472
Al Melvin.

553
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:35,234
Al, it's Ben Marco.
Are you in there?

554
00:31:40,240 --> 00:31:42,071
RAYMOND:
Fox is in the henhouse.

555
00:31:42,280 --> 00:31:43,952
Weasel.

556
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:48,276
Weasel is...

557
00:31:49,840 --> 00:31:51,910
The weasel is a weasel.

558
00:31:53,520 --> 00:31:55,158
Sir, I'll be right outside.

559
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:56,835
What?

560
00:31:57,520 --> 00:31:59,590
I'll be right outside, sir.

561
00:32:00,400 --> 00:32:01,719
I know.

562
00:32:02,400 --> 00:32:04,152
- Good night.
- Good night, sir.

563
00:32:04,360 --> 00:32:05,998
[PHONE RINGING]

564
00:32:06,200 --> 00:32:07,952
- Shall I get that for you, sir?
- No.

565
00:32:08,160 --> 00:32:10,196
- Good night, sir.
- Good night.

566
00:32:31,840 --> 00:32:34,035
You have 30 seconds, Mother.

567
00:32:34,240 --> 00:32:35,559
Am I that predictable?

568
00:32:35,840 --> 00:32:37,671
You have no idea.

569
00:32:37,920 --> 00:32:40,514
<i>I'm calling to compliment you,</i>
<i>Mr. Grumpy.</i>

570
00:32:40,720 --> 00:32:43,553
I thought you were
magnificent tonight.

571
00:32:43,800 --> 00:32:46,598
And so did all the network
campaign experts.

572
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:48,917
<i>And that compassionate</i>
<i>vigilance thing</i>

573
00:32:49,120 --> 00:32:50,519
[PHONE RINGING]

574
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:53,359
<i>Is working quite well for you.</i>

575
00:32:54,040 --> 00:32:56,918
- I might have to convert.
<i>- I happen to believe in it.</i>

576
00:32:57,120 --> 00:32:58,599
<i>Oh, yes, of course you do.</i>

577
00:32:58,840 --> 00:33:00,956
<i>- Now, Raymond...</i>
- Good night, Mother.

578
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:03,714
<i>Raymond? What? No, wait, wait.</i>

579
00:33:04,720 --> 00:33:06,836
- Hang on a second.
<i>- What? Raymond?</i>

580
00:33:07,320 --> 00:33:08,514
Are you there?

581
00:33:11,080 --> 00:33:12,433
Yes?

582
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:14,552
NOYLE:
<i>Sergeant Shaw?</i>

583
00:33:14,960 --> 00:33:16,598
Who is this?

584
00:33:17,280 --> 00:33:20,272
<i>- Sergeant Raymond Shaw?</i>
- Yes.

585
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:23,068
<i>Raymond Prentiss Shaw?</i>

586
00:33:28,120 --> 00:33:29,553
Yes.

587
00:33:29,840 --> 00:33:31,114
<i>Listen.</i>

588
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:33,159
<i>Go to the bedroom of your suite.</i>

589
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:36,914
<i>Enter the hallway there.</i>

590
00:33:37,120 --> 00:33:40,556
<i>Go to the end and open the closet.</i>

591
00:34:08,640 --> 00:34:10,756
Yes, thank you.

592
00:34:13,280 --> 00:34:15,748
- Hello, Raymond.
RAYMOND: Hello.

593
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:17,752
Do you remember me?

594
00:34:22,280 --> 00:34:23,679
No, sir, I don't.

595
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:26,394
Brilliant. We've got 20 minutes
for our little checkup

596
00:34:26,600 --> 00:34:29,319
from the neck up, gentlemen,
so if we could take his jacket.

597
00:34:29,520 --> 00:34:31,317
Please sit down.

598
00:34:34,240 --> 00:34:36,754
No, Mr. Villalobos, I'm just...
The Army's got me gathering

599
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:39,758
information on stress disorders,
so I'm just...

600
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:42,673
...you know, just running statistics,
trying to find out about my old team...

601
00:34:42,880 --> 00:34:44,836
[PHONE HANGS UP]

602
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:48,831
MARCO:
Well, listen. Mr. Wilson,

603
00:34:49,080 --> 00:34:53,312
when Nathan came home,
was he preoccupied with Kuwait?

604
00:34:53,520 --> 00:34:55,158
I mean, did he have nightmares
or bad dreams

605
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:56,998
about the firefight over there?

606
00:34:57,480 --> 00:34:59,152
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

607
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:06,037
NOYLE: You'll feel a little cold
as this anesthetic gel goes on.

608
00:35:10,840 --> 00:35:12,990
Probe sheath...

609
00:35:13,200 --> 00:35:15,919
...and probe.

610
00:35:19,360 --> 00:35:21,715
Please relax.
Are you relaxed, Raymond?

611
00:35:21,920 --> 00:35:22,989
Yes, sir.

612
00:35:23,240 --> 00:35:27,791
NOYLE: Now, Raymond,
I am going to drill a tiny hole in the skull,

613
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:31,709
which will allow delivery
of the new implant.

614
00:35:32,320 --> 00:35:35,232
So, what you'll feel is a little
discomfort in the form of pressure

615
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:37,715
and also a loud vibrating noise
in your head,

616
00:35:37,920 --> 00:35:41,708
all of which, of course,
is completely normal.

617
00:35:58,600 --> 00:36:00,556
[MAN SPEAKING
ON TELEVISION NEARBY]

618
00:36:02,640 --> 00:36:04,596
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING NEARBY]

619
00:37:38,760 --> 00:37:40,113
NOYLE:
<i>Thank you.</i>

620
00:37:42,720 --> 00:37:45,393
Of course, as soon as this
or any task is completed,

621
00:37:45,600 --> 00:37:50,310
you will already have forgotten
that it ever actually took place.

622
00:37:51,200 --> 00:37:53,077
Probe going in now.

623
00:37:55,120 --> 00:37:57,076
[MONITOR BEEPING]

624
00:38:02,560 --> 00:38:03,788
Good.

625
00:38:05,520 --> 00:38:07,238
Excellent.

626
00:38:07,440 --> 00:38:09,749
Releasing implant.

627
00:38:09,960 --> 00:38:12,349
There. That wasn't so bad,
was it, Raymond?

628
00:38:12,560 --> 00:38:13,788
No, sir.

629
00:38:14,440 --> 00:38:16,635
NOYLE:
That's good. No decay, no slippage.

630
00:38:16,840 --> 00:38:20,879
Everything seems to be
in flawless working condition.

631
00:38:45,680 --> 00:38:47,511
NOYLE:
Now, Raymond.

632
00:38:47,760 --> 00:38:51,150
Can you remember the deaths
of Private Baker and Private Ingram?

633
00:38:51,360 --> 00:38:52,315
RAYMOND:
Yes, sir.

634
00:38:52,560 --> 00:38:54,949
NOYLE: Good. Can you describe them
for me, please?

635
00:38:55,160 --> 00:38:58,072
RAYMOND: <i>We're on a routine recon</i>
<i>inside Iraqi-controlled terrain,</i>

636
00:38:58,280 --> 00:39:00,669
<i>assessing troop strength.</i>

637
00:39:02,080 --> 00:39:06,232
"We're on a routine recon
inside Iraqi-controlled terrain,

638
00:39:06,440 --> 00:39:07,759
assessing troop strength."

639
00:39:07,960 --> 00:39:10,474
The mission ends without incident.
We're heading back...

640
00:39:10,680 --> 00:39:13,319
"Toward the command.
The night is clear. Stars..."

641
00:39:13,560 --> 00:39:16,757
The night is clear.
Stars, but no moon.

642
00:39:17,320 --> 00:39:18,514
<i>The patrol is ambushed.</i>

643
00:39:18,720 --> 00:39:21,837
<i>We're engaged unexpectedly by</i>
<i>ground forces with helicopter support.</i>

644
00:39:22,040 --> 00:39:24,759
<i>RPG incoming, mortar fire.</i>

645
00:39:25,080 --> 00:39:26,559
"Captain..."

646
00:39:28,120 --> 00:39:30,350
Captain Marco
is knocked unconscious.

647
00:39:30,560 --> 00:39:34,314
In the ensuing firefight, Eddie Ingram
gets himself separated to the left.

648
00:39:35,040 --> 00:39:37,076
<i>Baker goes after him.</i>

649
00:39:37,280 --> 00:39:39,316
<i>An incoming mortar shell</i>
<i>kills them both instantly</i>

650
00:39:39,520 --> 00:39:42,796
<i>before I am able to locate and</i>
<i>eliminate the source of the ordnance.</i>

651
00:39:44,560 --> 00:39:47,791
MELVIN [WHISPERING]:
<i>Captain. Captain Marco.</i>

652
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:49,399
<i>Help me.</i>

653
00:39:56,760 --> 00:39:59,479
TOKAR:
Pardon me. Is this seat taken?

654
00:40:00,080 --> 00:40:03,470
I see the captain enjoys
the road less traveled.

655
00:40:20,240 --> 00:40:22,196
ROSIE:
Paper or plastic?

656
00:40:24,160 --> 00:40:27,277
Oh, come on.
From the grocery store.

657
00:40:27,480 --> 00:40:30,358
You know, at the checkout stand.
Paper or plastic girl, that's me.

658
00:40:30,560 --> 00:40:31,959
"Paper or plastic, sir?"

659
00:40:33,560 --> 00:40:34,913
I see you there all the time.

660
00:40:35,120 --> 00:40:37,509
Bennett Marco.
Checks from First National Bank.

661
00:40:37,720 --> 00:40:42,316
Romance novels, instant noodles,
NoDoz and tomatoes.

662
00:40:46,240 --> 00:40:48,913
So anyway, I'm on vacation.

663
00:40:49,120 --> 00:40:51,190
Holiday in the Big Apple
and all of that.

664
00:40:51,400 --> 00:40:53,709
And I saw you sitting here
and I said, "Hey,

665
00:40:53,920 --> 00:40:56,673
why not reach out
and touch someone?"

666
00:40:57,520 --> 00:40:58,509
Ha.

667
00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:03,118
So, what, I suppose
you're heading to New York City.

668
00:41:03,320 --> 00:41:05,356
Yeah, yeah, I'm... Yeah.

669
00:41:05,960 --> 00:41:08,269
Business? Pleasure? Both?

670
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:13,390
Well, I'm just... I got an old friend
up there, an old Army friend that...

671
00:41:14,320 --> 00:41:17,073
Well, he's in politics now
and I'm just gonna

672
00:41:17,280 --> 00:41:19,510
catch up on old times with him.

673
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:24,839
I'm sorry, you said your name was?

674
00:41:25,720 --> 00:41:27,073
Eugenie.

675
00:41:28,040 --> 00:41:29,553
What do your friends call you?

676
00:41:29,760 --> 00:41:31,796
My friends, they call me Rosie.

677
00:41:32,240 --> 00:41:34,151
- Rosie?
- Yeah, see, my full name is

678
00:41:34,360 --> 00:41:35,839
Eugenie Rose.
I like the Rosie part better.

679
00:41:36,040 --> 00:41:38,679
Eugenie is, well...

680
00:41:39,200 --> 00:41:40,679
...fragile.

681
00:41:41,040 --> 00:41:44,112
Yeah, but still, when I asked you
your name, you didn't say...

682
00:41:44,560 --> 00:41:46,357
What did you say?
You said Eugenie.

683
00:41:46,560 --> 00:41:48,630
Yeah, well...

684
00:41:49,200 --> 00:41:53,716
...maybe I was feeling fragile
at the time.

685
00:42:02,640 --> 00:42:04,039
Are you okay?

686
00:42:04,240 --> 00:42:05,514
Excuse me.

687
00:42:18,360 --> 00:42:19,759
[SIGHS]

688
00:42:51,680 --> 00:42:53,033
Hello, captain.

689
00:42:53,760 --> 00:42:55,113
Do you remember me?

690
00:43:01,080 --> 00:43:03,435
[SIREN WAILING]

691
00:43:06,240 --> 00:43:08,800
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
ON PA S YSTEM]

692
00:43:26,040 --> 00:43:27,314
Ben.

693
00:43:28,160 --> 00:43:31,470
Hey. I'm gonna get a cab.
You want me to drop you somewhere?

694
00:43:31,680 --> 00:43:32,669
No, I'm okay.

695
00:43:32,880 --> 00:43:34,757
Okay. So your friend's
gonna meet you here, then?

696
00:43:34,960 --> 00:43:36,279
No.

697
00:43:37,760 --> 00:43:39,113
All right.

698
00:43:39,320 --> 00:43:42,198
El Dorado 59970.

699
00:43:44,520 --> 00:43:48,149
It's my cell phone number,
in case you ever... You know.

700
00:43:48,360 --> 00:43:50,271
I like to say it the old-fashioned way.

