777
00:49:31,040 --> 00:49:34,237
<i>that the African nation's military</i>
<i>regime had secretly resumed</i>

778
00:49:34,440 --> 00:49:35,873
<i>its chemical weapons program.</i>

779
00:49:36,080 --> 00:49:38,310
<i>The secretary of defense declined</i>
<i>to comment on the attack,</i>

780
00:49:38,520 --> 00:49:40,317
<i>saying only that the mission</i>
<i>was successful,</i>

781
00:49:40,520 --> 00:49:43,432
<i>targets acquired, that all American</i>
<i>personnel involved here</i>

782
00:49:43,640 --> 00:49:44,914
<i>were home safe and sound.</i>

783
00:49:45,120 --> 00:49:47,873
RADIO NEWSCASTER 2:
<i>Striking transportation workers...</i>

784
00:49:48,080 --> 00:49:52,278
My dreams seem more real to me

785
00:49:52,480 --> 00:49:55,756
than what I actually remember
happening over there. It's like...

786
00:49:57,920 --> 00:50:03,119
It's like somewhere along the line
I got brainwashed or something and...

787
00:50:05,400 --> 00:50:08,039
I'm just, like, all scrambled up.

788
00:50:09,160 --> 00:50:11,116
We have all been
brainwashed, Marco.

789
00:50:12,280 --> 00:50:15,477
As for somebody
imbedding electric probes

790
00:50:15,680 --> 00:50:20,071
and computer chips in your brain
to make you do things,

791
00:50:20,320 --> 00:50:22,038
it's horseshit, man.

792
00:50:24,680 --> 00:50:26,033
A little electroshock...

793
00:50:26,960 --> 00:50:30,350
...and sleep deprivation will do
the trick for a fraction of the price.

794
00:50:30,560 --> 00:50:32,471
Ask the Uzbeks.

795
00:50:33,640 --> 00:50:35,517
What about my dreams?

796
00:50:36,800 --> 00:50:39,872
What if all this is your dream...

797
00:50:40,960 --> 00:50:43,758
...and you are really
still back in Kuwait?

798
00:50:47,840 --> 00:50:50,195
[SIRENS WAILING]

799
00:50:52,520 --> 00:50:54,875
[CROWD CHEERING]

800
00:51:06,720 --> 00:51:09,712
- Thanks for coming out. Thank you.
MAN: Congressman!

801
00:51:09,920 --> 00:51:11,433
- Congressman!
WOMAN: Congressman!

802
00:51:11,640 --> 00:51:14,200
Congressman! Congressman!
Why do you and Governor Arthur

803
00:51:14,400 --> 00:51:16,118
oppose deploying troops
into Indonesia?

804
00:51:16,320 --> 00:51:17,639
Well, Governor Arthur and I believe

805
00:51:17,840 --> 00:51:19,558
we can't clean up the world
with dirty hands.

806
00:51:19,760 --> 00:51:21,352
MARCO:
Sergeant Shaw!

807
00:51:23,040 --> 00:51:24,678
Do you ever dream about Kuwait?

808
00:51:25,000 --> 00:51:26,718
Captain Marco.

809
00:51:28,560 --> 00:51:30,232
It's okay. It's okay.

810
00:51:30,440 --> 00:51:31,873
Nice to see you, sir.

811
00:51:32,120 --> 00:51:34,395
Good evening.
It's good to see you too.

812
00:51:34,600 --> 00:51:35,919
Why did you ask me about Kuwait?

813
00:51:36,120 --> 00:51:37,599
I didn't.
I asked you about your dreams.

814
00:51:37,800 --> 00:51:39,153
- Thank you, Lily.
- Congressman Shaw, I'm sorry.

815
00:51:39,360 --> 00:51:41,635
They wanna know if you can do
an interview with Larry King at 6?

816
00:51:41,840 --> 00:51:43,319
- No, no.
- No to the interview or no to 6?

817
00:51:43,520 --> 00:51:44,953
No. He wants to talk
about my mother. No.

818
00:51:45,160 --> 00:51:46,912
- Everything under control, P. J?
- Hello, sir.

819
00:51:47,160 --> 00:51:48,752
RAYMOND:
Good to see you.

820
00:51:49,000 --> 00:51:50,672
So, captain, what can I do for you?

821
00:51:50,880 --> 00:51:52,359
I just need a few minutes
of your time.

822
00:51:52,560 --> 00:51:53,879
Congressman Shaw,
a moment, please?

823
00:51:54,080 --> 00:51:55,035
Private time.

824
00:51:55,240 --> 00:51:57,754
Unfortunately, this is as private
as it gets for me now.

825
00:51:57,960 --> 00:51:59,439
- I understand.
- He's all right, Will.

826
00:51:59,640 --> 00:52:01,551
- Come on in.
MARCO: Thank you, thank you.

827
00:52:03,040 --> 00:52:05,600
RAYMOND: Hey, George.
- There are these dreams

828
00:52:05,800 --> 00:52:08,439
that some of the men
from our unit have been having.

829
00:52:08,640 --> 00:52:09,914
Including you?

830
00:52:10,120 --> 00:52:11,348
Well...

831
00:52:11,960 --> 00:52:14,872
...it's more of a question
of what actually happened

832
00:52:15,080 --> 00:52:17,036
the night that our patrol
got attacked.

833
00:52:17,560 --> 00:52:21,633
That's easy. We're on a routine recon
inside Iraqi-controlled terrain.

834
00:52:21,840 --> 00:52:24,354
The patrol is ambushed.
RPG incoming, mortar fire.

835
00:52:24,560 --> 00:52:26,676
- You're knocked...
- Unconscious. Exactly the way...

836
00:52:26,880 --> 00:52:29,713
Not to cut you off, but I mean,
exactly the way that I remember it.

837
00:52:29,920 --> 00:52:32,593
But I dreamed something else.

838
00:52:34,160 --> 00:52:35,593
Am I in your dreams, captain?

839
00:52:36,480 --> 00:52:38,038
Yes, you are, congressman.

840
00:52:38,360 --> 00:52:39,429
Saving everybody?

841
00:52:39,640 --> 00:52:42,518
It's a whole lot more complicated
than that. Now, Corporal Melvin,

842
00:52:42,720 --> 00:52:45,075
he's been drawing these pictures
and he wrote down what he dreams.

843
00:52:45,280 --> 00:52:47,794
- Maybe if you just...
- I don't have dreams, captain.

844
00:52:48,000 --> 00:52:50,594
At all? You don't dream at all?
Everybody dreams, right? I mean...

845
00:52:50,800 --> 00:52:53,234
Look, captain, I'd like to help you,
I would, I really would,

846
00:52:53,440 --> 00:52:54,953
but I think you ought to
see somebody.

847
00:52:55,160 --> 00:52:57,310
- Somebody who specializes in...
- I've been to doctors.

848
00:52:57,800 --> 00:52:59,313
Well, good, that's very good,

849
00:52:59,520 --> 00:53:01,875
because they can probably
help you out a lot more than I can.

850
00:53:02,080 --> 00:53:03,798
- I don't know, but...
- Take care, captain.

851
00:53:04,000 --> 00:53:06,468
- Yeah. Yeah. Okay.
- Thanks for coming by.

852
00:53:12,680 --> 00:53:14,352
I'm not crazy, Shaw.

853
00:53:18,400 --> 00:53:19,879
Major.

854
00:53:22,000 --> 00:53:25,709
- Ben. Are you hungry?
- Starving.

855
00:53:31,040 --> 00:53:32,473
Well, it depends on the demographic.

856
00:53:32,720 --> 00:53:33,948
WOMAN:
Excuse me.

857
00:53:35,400 --> 00:53:37,231
- I killed Baker?
MARCO: Well, it's a dream.

858
00:53:37,440 --> 00:53:39,476
I mean, it could mean
something else.

859
00:53:39,960 --> 00:53:42,190
It could mean I'm supposed
to think you did.

860
00:53:42,400 --> 00:53:46,075
No, I killed the enemy.
I didn't know them either, so...

861
00:53:46,440 --> 00:53:48,032
...it was okay.

862
00:53:48,760 --> 00:53:51,558
And anyway, I remember what we did
in Kuwait. I remember it perfectly.

863
00:53:51,760 --> 00:53:52,909
I just...

864
00:53:53,440 --> 00:53:55,749
...don't remember actually doing it.

865
00:53:56,480 --> 00:53:58,072
Maybe you didn't do it.

866
00:54:04,800 --> 00:54:06,233
No.

867
00:54:07,200 --> 00:54:08,713
What a thought.

868
00:54:26,080 --> 00:54:27,479
What?

869
00:54:32,080 --> 00:54:34,036
Life is so bizarre, isn't it?

870
00:54:35,040 --> 00:54:36,598
Which part?

871
00:54:36,800 --> 00:54:39,155
I don't know.
What you saw downstairs.

872
00:54:39,600 --> 00:54:45,277
This campaign. Politics.
My whole public life and persona.

873
00:54:46,760 --> 00:54:50,389
I mean, posing and grinning
like a goddamn sock puppet,

874
00:54:50,600 --> 00:54:53,160
shaking hands with total strangers
who must be completely blind

875
00:54:53,360 --> 00:54:55,635
if they can't see
what I am at the core.

876
00:54:55,840 --> 00:54:58,673
What my mother has made me.
A Prentiss.

877
00:54:58,880 --> 00:55:01,030
Ferociously a Prentiss.

878
00:55:01,600 --> 00:55:04,751
- But not a Shaw. No, sir.
- I see.

879
00:55:05,280 --> 00:55:06,793
No, you don't.

880
00:55:07,720 --> 00:55:08,869
You can't.

881
00:55:11,240 --> 00:55:13,117
I was 20 years old
before I had a friend.

882
00:55:13,320 --> 00:55:19,077
Worse, a girlfriend. Well, you know,
from my point of view, anyway.

883
00:55:19,440 --> 00:55:23,149
A friend outside of my mother's circle
of approved encounters

884
00:55:23,360 --> 00:55:25,396
and she...

885
00:55:27,680 --> 00:55:29,318
...my mother...

886
00:55:29,760 --> 00:55:31,432
[CLEARS THROAT]

887
00:55:32,280 --> 00:55:36,558
God only knows what she told
Jocelyn to chase her away.

888
00:55:37,080 --> 00:55:39,594
Precipitating my sole act
of rebellion:

889
00:55:39,800 --> 00:55:41,552
Storming off...

890
00:55:42,320 --> 00:55:44,709
...and enlisting in the Army.

891
00:55:48,000 --> 00:55:49,353
But after the war...

892
00:55:51,280 --> 00:55:53,396
...I came back to her.

893
00:55:55,000 --> 00:55:57,070
Why did you come back?
What happened?

894
00:56:01,520 --> 00:56:03,238
Weren't you listening?

895
00:56:03,920 --> 00:56:05,797
Mother happened.

896
00:56:06,960 --> 00:56:09,076
You know, the truth is I hate it.

897
00:56:09,520 --> 00:56:11,715
I've always despised the Medal.

898
00:56:12,320 --> 00:56:15,517
The cloying adulation
of the little people.

899
00:56:16,480 --> 00:56:18,675
It's certainly...

900
00:56:18,920 --> 00:56:21,388
...nothing for you
to be jealous of, major.

901
00:56:21,600 --> 00:56:22,919
I'm not jealous.

902
00:56:23,840 --> 00:56:25,558
I don't have the dreams, Ben.

903
00:56:26,040 --> 00:56:30,192
How could you not remember
saving our unit?

904
00:56:30,760 --> 00:56:32,113
I do. I said I did.

905
00:56:32,320 --> 00:56:35,756
No, no, you didn't. You said
that you didn't remember doing it.

906
00:56:35,960 --> 00:56:38,190
That's what you just said
a couple minutes ago.

907
00:56:39,840 --> 00:56:41,956
When I think about that night...

908
00:56:43,520 --> 00:56:46,034
...it's as if I know what will happen.

909
00:56:47,240 --> 00:56:48,958
The thing is, I never seem
to get to the point

910
00:56:49,160 --> 00:56:52,152
where I feel that it actually
does happen.

911
00:56:52,360 --> 00:56:54,112
But I'm sure that's perfectly normal.

912
00:56:54,400 --> 00:56:57,870
Okay. Well, have you discussed this
with anyone? These discrepancies?

913
00:56:58,240 --> 00:57:00,310
Who would I share that with?

914
00:57:01,040 --> 00:57:03,315
My old Army buddies
who love and adore me

915
00:57:03,520 --> 00:57:05,556
for saving their
pathetically unimportant,

916
00:57:05,760 --> 00:57:08,115
present company excluded, asses?

917
00:57:08,560 --> 00:57:10,516
You could discuss it
with Army intelligence.

918
00:57:10,720 --> 00:57:13,996
You could go down there.
I mean, I could go with you

919
00:57:14,200 --> 00:57:16,270
and discuss it and you can tell them
what you remember,

920
00:57:16,480 --> 00:57:19,313
what you don't remember,
and they could...

921
00:57:20,040 --> 00:57:21,712
...run some tests.

922
00:57:24,360 --> 00:57:26,669
Yeah, tests. Boy.

923
00:57:26,880 --> 00:57:28,791
The press would have
a field day with that.

924
00:57:29,440 --> 00:57:32,034
Somebody put an implant inside me.
I found it this morning.

925
00:57:32,240 --> 00:57:34,356
I've got the hole in my back
if you wanna take a look at it.

926
00:57:34,560 --> 00:57:37,028
And I got a good feeling
they put one in you too.

927
00:57:42,840 --> 00:57:44,432
Nobody has put anything
in me, Ben.

928
00:57:44,640 --> 00:57:46,676
Let's prove it.
Why don't, you know...

929
00:57:46,880 --> 00:57:48,393
- We'll go get an x-ray...
- Look, Ben,

930
00:57:48,600 --> 00:57:50,318
I wanna be supportive of you. I do.

931
00:57:50,520 --> 00:57:52,988
But don't you think this could wait
till after the election?

932
00:57:53,200 --> 00:57:54,315
Why? For what?

933
00:57:54,520 --> 00:57:56,476
- What are you scared of?
- I'm not afraid of anything.

934
00:57:56,680 --> 00:57:59,319
- Then why don't we just prove it...
- Know what? I think you should leave.

935
00:57:59,520 --> 00:58:01,988
- I'm sorry, I really...
- Listen.

936
00:58:02,200 --> 00:58:06,796
Somebody got into our heads
with big steel-toe boots,

937
00:58:07,000 --> 00:58:09,355
cable cutters and a chainsaw
and they went to town.

938
00:58:09,560 --> 00:58:12,870
Neurons got... Got...
Got exposed and circuits got rewired.

939
00:58:13,080 --> 00:58:15,674
Our brain cells got
obliterated, Raymond.

940
00:58:15,880 --> 00:58:17,393
Please.

941
00:58:18,240 --> 00:58:20,117
You need to get help, Ben.

942
00:58:20,920 --> 00:58:23,036
What are you doing? Ben!

